title._content: Students in the Courtyard of Senior High School at New Ulm Minnesota ..., 10/1974

description._content: Original Caption: Students in the Courtyard of Senior High School at New Ulm Minnesota. The Town Is a County Seat Trading Center of 13,000 in a Farming Area of South Central Minnesota. It Was Founded in 1854 by a German Immigrant Land Company That Encouraged Its Kinsmen to Emigrate From Europe. Several Manufacturing Firms Have Arrived Since 1950 and Have Helped the Town to Grow. The Business District Was Revitalized in the 1960's with Community Effort 10/1974 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 412-DA-15761 Photographer: Rees, David, 1943- Subjects: New Ulm (Brown county, Minnesota, United States) inhabited place Environmental Protection Agency Project DOCUMERICA Persistent URL: arcweb.archives.gov/arc/action/ExternalIdSearch?id=558211 Repository: Still Picture Records Section, Special Media Archives Services Division (NWCS-S), National Archives at College Park, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, MD, 20740-6001.
